# CODEOWNERS — human review gates for the Hitchhiker's Guide
#
# The Living Guide is bot-driven (Assayer, Gardener, Miner, Scout, etc.) but
# the human maintainer remains editor of last resort. Anything that touches
# the canonical guide prose, sources of truth, or contributor-facing process
# requires explicit human sign-off before merge.
#
# Combine this file with branch protection on `main` requiring CODEOWNER
# review on matching paths.
#
# Syntax: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-customizations/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default: no owner. Most paths can be merged by the merge queue without
# explicit human approval. Add specific rules below for paths that MUST be
# reviewed by a human.

# The Guide itself — every chapter, plus SOURCES.md.
# Bots may draft, but a human ships.
/guide/                 @steveash
/guide/**               @steveash
